    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I believe it'd be possible to use `METH_FASTCALL` in Limited API >= 3.10 with non-cyfunctions (i.e. binding=False`).\n\nThat would make calls from Python more efficient, it probably wouldn't make calls from Cython worse, and it's possible we could do something clever with optimized paths to make calls from Cython better too.\n\nHowever: I'm not convinced we *should* do this. I don't think we want to push people towards using `binding=False` since it's generally a worse experience in other ways. I'm opening this issue in case any Limited API users feel very strongly different and want to comment to try to persuade us otherwise.",
